==Appearance==
'''Level 829, also known as “Cherry Dusk“, is described as a big complex of suburban neighbourhoods resembling typical American residential areas constructed between the late 1990s and early 2000s. The level consists of wide streets, detached houses with driveways, small front lawns, and evenly spaced sidewalks. Parks and forests are scattered throughout the level and are present within the neighbourhoods.'''
{{Blurimage|file=Level 829 new.jpg|caption=“A picture of a neighbourhood in Level 829”}}
'''The entire level is enveloped in a deep red sky, casting a constant crimson glow over the environment. The time appears to be fixed in an unnatural state between late dusk and early night. The sky emits a dim reddish glow that provides limited visibility.'''

'''Streetlights line the roads and are quite common. They always emit either a deep crimson light or a bright white light. The lighting has no discernible pattern, creating uneven patches of illumination along streets and sidewalks.'''

'''The neighbourhood appears to resemble american style, with houses, garages, and fenced backyards arranged in familiar suburban layouts. However, no inhabitants have ever been observed, and all buildings appear abandoned. Occasionally, lights may be visible inside homes, but no movement or sound accompanies them.'''

'''The layout of Level 829 subtly shifts when not directly observed. Roads may curve differently, intersections may appear or disappear, and certain streets may loop back to previously visited areas. These changes are gradual and often go unnoticed until navigation becomes unreliable.'''

'''Road conditions vary unpredictably. Some streets are smooth and newly paved, while others are cracked, uneven, or very sloped. These transitions can occur without warning, making walking disorienting and potentially hazardous.'''
{{Blurimage|file=Level 829 new2.png|caption=“A recent picture of a neighbourhood in Level 829.”|align=left}}
'''The houses in Level 829 follow typical suburban designs, usually consisting of one to two floors with attached garages and small fenced backyards. The interiors often resemble normal homes at first glance, containing common furniture such as sofas, beds, kitchen appliances, and dining tables. However, the layout inside is frequently inconsistent, with rooms appearing slightly distorted, compressed, or arranged in impractical ways. Furniture within these houses behaves unpredictably. Objects may shift slightly when not observed, and in some cases, furniture can collapse without warning. Despite this, certain houses may still contain useful items such as food, basic supplies, or a place to relax.'''

'''Cars are randomly parked along the sides of the roads, usually on the right. The car brands do not exist in The Frontrooms. Most cars are unlocked, but they are neither drivable nor towable. They appear locked in place with no way to move them. Snacks can sometimes be found inside car trunks.'''

'''The air quality in Level 829 is poor, especially inside houses and garages. The air feels heavy and slightly harder to breathe, often with a faint, unusual smell. Spending too much time indoors can cause headaches, dizziness, or fatigue.'''

'''The overall temperature varies slightly from place to place, generally ranging between 11°C (51.8°F) and 17°C (62.6°F). The temperature stays fairly stable overall, without any clear day or night changes.'''
<center>
==Environment==
'''Level 829 has dim, stagnant, and poor air quality conditions that persist throughout the level, with temperatures typically ranging between 11°C (51.8°F) and 17°C (62.6°F). The air often feels heavy and slightly difficult to breathe, especially in enclosed spaces such as houses and garages, where ventilation appears limited or ineffective. A faint, unusual odor is sometimes present, though its source is unknown.'''

'''These environmental conditions may fluctuate slightly without clear warning, though not as drastically as other levels. In some cases, the air may become more dense or stale over short periods of time, increasing discomfort and making prolonged exposure indoors more difficult to tolerate. Wanderers may begin to experience mild symptoms such as headaches, fatigue, or dizziness after extended periods within poorly ventilated areas.'''

'''Open areas such as streets and parks generally have slightly better air circulation, though the overall quality remains low.'''
===Air Quality Analysis===

<div class="meg-fandom-logoblock">
[[File:M.E.G without the text.png|center|150px]]
<center>''M.E.G. analysis, 2021''</center>
<br>
<div style="text-align:center">The primary threat to everyone who enters '''Level 829''', is poor air quality. The quality of the air does vary in some areas, but even in small doses can be harmful. Via sampling, M.E.G. operatives were able to determine some pollutants of the air quality, although there could be additional undiscovered ones in the skies. Common elements present in the sky are as follows:
</div>
*Sulfur dioxide
*Nitrogen dioxide
*Carbon Dioxide
*Carbon Monoxide
*Nitrogen Oxide
*Methane (CH₄)
*PM<sup>2.5</sup>
*Ozone
<div style="text-align:center"> After long exposure, one might start to notice irritation or mild headaches. This gets worst over time. Common symptoms are as follows:</div>
===Common symptoms===
*Headaches
*Extreme coughing
*Fatigue
*Dry eyes
*Nose or throat irritation

<div style="text-align:center">Furthermore, prolonged exposure to the air quality of the level can lead to a stroke or heart attack. These symptoms will immediately stop after exiting '''Level 829'''. It's advised to always wear a gas mask that can filter out the pollutants of the air quality, In addition, eyewear, for example, goggles, are recommended to prevent particles from entering one's eyes.</div>


<div style="text-align:center">Although the households have slightly better air quality, it is still advised to lock any doors or windows.</div>
</div>

==Entities==
[[Entity 2|Windows]] inhabit the households, usually inside the basements. No entities have been confirmed lurking outside of the houses have been found.

==Colonies & Outposts==
Wanderers can meet each other in '''Level 829,''' establishing colonies or outposts is nearly impossible due to '''Level 829's''' dangerous atmosphere and conditions.
==Entrances & Exits==
===Entrances===
*'''Finding a house in [[Level 9]] with completely red-tinted windows and entering it has a low chance of leading here.'''
*'''Nocliping through a bed on [[Level 69]] will lead here.'''
*'''Grabbing a red lamp in [[Level 168]] will lead here.'''
*'''Opening any red door have a very low chance of leading here.'''
*'''Jumping into a fire on any level will lead here. (NOT RECOMMENDED)'''
===Exits===
*'''Finding a book with a title 827 will lead to [[Level 827]].'''
*'''Entering a maintenance tunnel will lead to [[Level 2]].'''
*'''Breaking a window in any house will lead to [[Level 330]].'''
*'''Entering an orange house will lead to [[Level 38]].'''
